@startuml Wave_Activity_Diagram
title Wave — Activity Diagram (live quiz-sync loop)

|Student App|
start
:Open topic ▶ Take quiz;
repeat
  :Answer current question;
repeat while (All questions answered?) is (No)
->Yes;
:Submit ▶ grade locally;
:Optimistic setProgressRecords\n(score / 10 shows instantly);
:repo.saveQuizAttempt;
:codec.encode ▶ tokenized envelope\n(direction = up);
if (Online?) then (No)
  :Outbox: queue write\n(localStorage / IndexedDB);
  note right: flushed on reconnect\nvia Outbox.flushAsync
  stop
else (Yes)
  :POST /api/sync/push\n(Authorization: Token);
endif

|Django Server|
:codec.decode_envelope;
:Zod / DRF serializer validate;
:persist QuizAttempt\n(upsert by student + topic);
:derive.compute_rankings\n+ assemble_progress;
:mqtt.publish_downstream\n(qos=1, retain=true, direction=down);

|MQTT Broker (LAN :9001)|
:Broker fan-out by topic;
fork
  :wave/<section>/StudentProgress;
fork again
  :wave/<section>/Rankings;
end fork

|Teacher App|
:MqttTransport receives (ws://host:9001);
note right
  A teacher that was offline gets the
  RETAINED message on reconnect
  ("delivered when reachable").
end note
:codec.decode + Zod validate\n(ignore direction=up echoes);
:applyRepoUpdate;
:setProgressRecords;
:Class Records + Rankings\nre-render live — no refresh;
stop

@enduml
